Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 12/2018]
Title: SUPPLEMENTAL RESTRAINT SYSTEMS: AIRBAG SYSTEM: B1622/81,B1623/81,B1632/81,B1633/81,B1642/81,B1643/81,B166D/81,B166E/81; Lost communication with Side Airbag Sensor RH; 2016 - 2018 MY Prius [11/2015 - 12/2018]

DTC

B1622/81

Lost communication with Side Airbag Sensor RH

DTC

B1623/81

Side Airbag Sensor Assembly RH Initialization Incomplete

DTC

B1632/81

Lost Communication with Rear Airbag Sensor RH

DTC

B1633/81

Rear Airbag Sensor Assembly RH Initialization Incomplete

DTC

B1642/81

Lost Communication with Side Satellite Sensor Bus RH

DTC

B1643/81

Side Satellite Sensor Bus RH Initialization Incomplete

DTC

B166D/81

Lost Communication with Front Door Pressure Sensor RH

DTC

B166E/81

Front Door Pressure Sensor RH Initialization Incomplete

DESCRIPTION

The side collision sensor RH circuit consists of the airbag ECU assembly, door side airbag sensor RH, side airbag sensor assembly RH and rear airbag sensor RH.

The door side airbag sensor RH, side airbag sensor assembly RH and rear airbag sensor RH detect impacts to the vehicle and send signals to the airbag ECU assembly to determine if the airbags and pretensioners should be deployed.

These DTCs are stored when a malfunction is detected in the side collision sensor RH circuit.

DTC No.

Detection Item

DTC Detection Condition

Trouble Area

Test Mode / Check Mode

B1622/81

Lost communication with Side Airbag Sensor RH

  • The airbag ECU assembly detects a line short, short to ground or B+, or an open in the side collision sensor RH circuit.
  • Side airbag sensor assembly RH malfunction
  • Rear airbag sensor RH malfunction
  • Door side airbag sensor RH malfunction
  • Airbag ECU assembly malfunction
  • Floor wire
  • Front door wire RH
  • Side airbag sensor assembly RH
  • Rear airbag sensor RH
  • Door side airbag sensor RH
  • Airbag ECU assembly

Does not apply to test/check mode

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

NOTICE:

After turning the power switch off, waiting time may be required before disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal. Therefore, make sure to read the disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal notices before proceeding with work.

PROCEDURE

1.

CHECK CURRENT DTC

(a) Check for current DTCs.

Click here

Body Electrical > SRS Airbag > Trouble Codes

HINT:

  • DTCs indicating communication errors will be changed to DTCs indicating errors in initialization by turning the power switch off and then on (IG) again.
  • Codes other than current DTCs B1622, B1623, B1632, B1633, B1642, B1643, B166D, B166E and 81 may be output at this time, but they are not related to this check.

Result

Proceed to

Current DTC B1642, B1643 or 81 is output.

A

Current DTC B1623 is output.

B

Current DTC B1633 is output.

C

Current DTC B166D or B166E is output.

D

Current DTC B1622 is output.

E

Current DTC B1632 is output.

F

Current DTCs B1622, B1623, B1632, B1633, B1642, B1643, B166D, B166E and 81 are not output.

USE SIMULATION METHOD TO CHECK

A

2.

CHECK CONNECTORS

(a) Turn the power switch off.

(b) Disconnect the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal.

CAUTION:

Wait at least 90 seconds after disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal to disable the SRS system.

(c) Check that the connectors are properly connected to the airbag ECU assembly, side airbag sensor assembly RH, rear airbag sensor RH and door side airbag sensor RH. Also check that the connectors that link the floor wire and front door wire RH are properly connected.

OK:

The connectors are properly connected.

HINT:

If the connectors are not properly connected, reconnect the connectors and proceed to the next inspection.

(d) Disconnect the connectors from the airbag ECU assembly, side airbag sensor assembly RH, rear airbag sensor RH and door side airbag sensor RH. Also disconnect the connectors that link the floor wire and front door wire RH.

(e) Check that the terminals of the connectors are not deformed or damaged.

OK:

The terminals are not deformed or damaged.

15.

CHECK SIDE AIRBAG SENSOR ASSEMBLY RH

(a) Connect the connectors to the rear airbag sensor RH, door side airbag sensor RH and airbag ECU assembly.

*1

Side Airbag Sensor Assembly LH

*2

Airbag ECU Assembly

(b) Interchange the side airbag sensor assembly RH with LH and connect the connectors.

(c) Connect the cable to the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal.

(d) Clear the DTCs stored in memory.

Click here

Body Electrical > SRS Airbag > Clear DTCs

(e) Turn the power switch off.

(f) Turn the power switch on (IG), and wait for at least 60 seconds.

(g) Check for DTCs.

Click here

Body Electrical > SRS Airbag > Trouble Codes

HINT:

Codes other than DTCs B1642, B1643, B1647, B1648, 81 and 82 may be output at this time, but they are not related to this check.

Result

Proceed to

DTC B1642, B1643 or 81 is output.

A

DTC B1647, B1648 or 82 is output.

B

DTCs B1642, B1643, B1647, B1648, 81 and 82 are not output.

C

(h) Turn the power switch off.

(i) Disconnect the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal.

CAUTION:

Wait at least 90 seconds after disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal to disable the SRS system.

(j) Return the side airbag sensor assembly RH and LH to their original positions and connect the connectors.
